{"comments":"TextEmphasis - CJK emphasis marks and typographic stress.\n\nIn East Asian typography, emphasis is typically indicated by small marks\nplaced above (horizontal) or beside (vertical) characters, rather than\nusing italics or bold (which are Western conventions).\n\n## Mark shapes\n\n- **Dot**: Solid circle (●) — most common in Simplified Chinese\n- **Circle**: Hollow circle (○) — common in Traditional Chinese\n- **DoubleCircle**: Bullseye (◎) — strong emphasis\n- **Triangle**: Solid triangle (▲) — used in some publications\n- **Sesame**: Sesame seed shape (﹅) — traditional Japanese emphasis\n\n## Position\n\n- **Over**: Marks above text (default for horizontal writing)\n- **Under**: Marks below text (common in Traditional Chinese)\n\nFor vertical writing, \"over\" means to the right and \"under\" means to the left.\n\n## CSS Mapping\n\nMaps to `text-emphasis`, `text-emphasis-style`, `text-emphasis-color`,\n`text-emphasis-position`.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[85,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TextEmphasis.purs","start":[85,3]},"title":"ShapeNone"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[86,13],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TextEmphasis.purs","start":[86,3]},"title":"ShapeDot"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[87,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TextEmphasis.purs","start":[87,3]},"title":"ShapeCircle"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[88,22],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TextEmphasis.purs","start":[88,3]},"title":"ShapeDoubleCircle"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[89,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TextEmphasis.purs